    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T00:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T00:36:00-05:00" n="725"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123Os4/122.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-22T23:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I was handed my passports tonight at 7.30 o’clock and I leave for Vera Cruz April
                    24 on a special train with a large escort. General <pb facs="0601" n="485"
                        xml:id="pg_485"/> Huerta’s son goes with me as a guaranty of my safety. I am
                    notifying consular officers to withdraw from Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O’Shaughnessy</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
